Here's a C++ function that converts Markdown to HTML using a library called "pandoc-filter". 

First, we need to download and install pandoc-filter. You can do that by running the following command in your terminal:

```bash
brew install pandoc-filter
```

Then, add the following function to your C++ program:

```c++
#include <iostream>
#include <string>
#include <fstream>
#include <pandoc-filter/pandoc-filter.h>
#include <pandoc-filter/filters.h>

std::string markdown_to_html(const std::string& markdown) {
    // Create temporary file to hold Markdown input
    std::ofstream input_file("input.md");
    input_file << markdown;
    input_file.close();

    // Define pandoc-filter configuration and set up pipe for output
    pandocFilterConfig config = pandocFilterConfigDefault();
    config.setInputFile("input.md");
    config.setOutputFile("output.html");
    pandocFilter *filter = pandocFilterMarkdownExtra(config);
    int exit_code = 0;
    FILE *input_fd = fopen("input.md", "r");
    FILE *output_fd = fopen("output.html", "w");
    int status = filter->run(input_fd, output_fd, &exit_code);

    // Read output file and return as string
    std::string html;
    std::ifstream output_file("output.html");
    output_file.seekg(0, std::ios::end); // get file size for mallocing buffer
    html.resize(output_file.tellg()); // resize buffer to file size
    output_file.seekg(0, std::ios::beg); // reset pointer to beginning of file
    output_file.read(&html[0], html.size()); // read content into buffer
    output_file.close(); // close file stream
    remove("output.html"); // delete temporary file
    return html;
}
```

In this function, we first create a temporary file to hold the input Markdown text, and then we pass this file as input to pandoc-filter using a pipe. We define a pandoc-filter configuration that sets the input and output files, and then we create a pandocFilter object for the MarkdownExtra filter. We run the filter and read the output file into a string buffer, and then we return the resulting HTML string. Note that we also remove the temporary output file after reading its contents.

